OL,3,C'Self preservation' stopping victims
OL,4,Cfrom getting answers, disaster expert
OL,5,Csays
OL,7,FBritain's leading disaster expert has
OL,8,Fsaid more needs to be done to keep
OL,9,Fpublic venues safe from terror and
OL,10,Ftragedy.
OL,12,FProfessor Lucy Easthope, a global
OL,13,Fadvisor in emergency planning and
OL,14,Fdisaster recovery, told Granada
OL,15,FReports: "There are lessons out there
OL,16,Fthat still need to be learned."
OL,18,FShe added: "I always say there are two
OL,19,Fsounds in the immediate aftermath of
OL,20,Ftragedy the sirens and the shredders.
