OL,3,C'Self preservation' stopping victims
OL,4,Cfrom getting answers, disaster expert
OL,5,Csays
OL,7,FShe said: "The families and
OL,8,Fcommunities are often so intuitive.
OL,9,FThey often know exactly what
OL,10,Foriginally went wrong, and sometimes
OL,11,Fthey're quite forgiving of that in the
OL,12,Fearly stages.
OL,14,F"They understand these events are
OL,15,Fmessy and complex, and particularly
OL,16,Fwith terror... they're up for honesty
OL,17,Fat that point.
OL,19,F"But what happens is, as the cover up
OL,20,Fcontinues over time, they lose any
OL,21,Ffaith they had in the responders."
